      "altText": "Case Temperature Rise vs. Load Current for LT7153SP. The curve shows a nonlinear (approximately quadratic) rise from 0°C at 0A to about 16°C at 25A.",
      "imageDescription": "The x-axis is I_OUT in amperes ranging from 0A to 25A. The y-axis is Case Temperature Rise in °C ranging from 0°C to 25°C. A single green/teal curve shows a nonlinear, upward-curving relationship between output current and case temperature rise. The temperature rise is near 0°C at low currents and increases approximately quadratically to about 16°C at 25A output current.",
