  "sections": [
    {
      "title": "Features",
      "type": "bullets",
      "items": [
        "Silent Switcher®2 Architecture",
        "Ultralow EMI",
        "Eliminates PCB Layout Sensitivity",
        "Internal Bypass Caps Reduce Radiated EMI",
        "SVIN: 2.7V to 5V; PVIN: 1.5V to 5V",
        "VOUT: 0.4V to 0.9VIN (LT7153SPAV-0.4); 0.5V to 0.9VIN (LT7153SPAV)",
        "Accurate Reference:",
        "0.4V ±1.0% Over Temp (LT7153SPAV-0.4)",
        "0.5V ±0.8% Over Temp (LT7153SPAV)",
        "Integrated N-MOSFETs: 1.8mΩ/0.7mΩ",
        "15ns Min On-Time: Low Duty Cycle Operation",
        "Differential VOUT Remote Sense",
        "Configurable Fixed Output Options",
        "Programmable Load Line (3 settings)",
        "Programmable Current Limit (3 settings)",
        "Programmable, Synchronizable: 400kHz to 5MHz",
        "User Selectable Discontinuous Mode® (DCM) or Forced Continuous Mode (FCM) Operation",
        "Controlled TON, Current Mode: Excellent Transient",
        "Power Good status, Output Tracking, Clock-Out",
        "Supports Spread Spectrum Operation",
        "PolyPhase Operation: 2, 3, 4, 6, 8 or 12 Phases",
        "36-Lead (4mm x 7mm) Exposed Back LQFN Package"
      ],
      "docOrder": 0
    },
    {
      "title": "Applications",
      "type": "bullets",
      "items": [
        "Optical Module Applications",
        "Distributed Power Systems, Server Power",
        "POINT-OF-LOAD SUPPLY (I.E., ASIC, FPGA, DSP, µP)"
      ],
      "docOrder": 1
    },
    {
      "title": "Description",
      "type": "text",
      "content": "The LT®7153SP is a high efficiency monolithic synchronous, Silent Switcher®2 buck regulator capable of delivering ±25A to the load. The unique constant frequency, controlled on-time, current mode architecture is ideal for high step-down ratio applications that operate at high frequencies while demanding fast transient response. PolyPhase operation allows multiple LT7153SP regulators to run out-of-phase, which reduces the amount of input and output capacitors needed while enables paralleling for higher output currents. The operating supply voltage range is from 2.7V to 5V.\n\nThe operating frequency is programmable from 400kHz to 5MHz with an external resistor or sync to an external clock signal. The high frequency capability allows the use of physically smaller inductors and capacitors.\n\nThe LT7153SP package features the second-generation Silent Switcher architecture to minimize EMI emissions while delivering high efficiency at high switching frequencies. This includes the integration of bypass capacitors to optimize high frequency current loops and makes it easy to achieve advertised EMI performance by reducing layout sensitivity. It also features an exposed back for heat sink attachment, which can be used to significantly improve thermal performance.\n\nSee Figure 27 for the operation when VOUT is lower than VREF.",
      "docOrder": 2
    },
    {
      "title": "Typical Application",
      "type": "text",
      "content": "",
      "altText": "Typical application schematic for the LT7153SP configured as a 0.5V, ±25A buck regulator with input voltage range of 2.7V to 5V.",
      "imageDescription": "The schematic shows the LT7153SP in a complete buck regulator application with VIN ranging from 2.7V to 5V connected to the SW and PV_IN pins. Input and output bulk capacitors are shown along with an output inductor. Key configuration pins including RUN, FB, PGOOD, MODE, SYNC/SPREAD, RT, ITH, SGND, AVPSEL, CLKOUT, TRACKSS, PHSMOD2/LIM, PHSMOD1/SEL are labeled. A 4.7µF bypass capacitor is shown on the INT_VCC pin, and resistors on RT and ITH set switching frequency and compensation. The output is labeled VOUT = 0.5V at ±25A.",
      "docOrder": 3
    },
