    {
      "tableTitle": "Package Information",
      "columns": [
        "COLUMN_1"
      ],
      "rows": [
        {
          "COLUMN_1": "LQFN PACKAGE 36-LEAD (4mm x 7mm x 1.02mm) TJMAX = 125 °C, θJA = 15.8°C/W (BASED ON DEMOBOARD), θJCtop = 0.4°C/W, θJCbot = 3.4°C/W EXPOSED PAD (PIN 37) AND CORNER PINS (38~41) ARE GND, MUST BE SOLDERED TO PCB Pin Configurations"
        }
      ],
      "docOrder": 6
    },
    {
      "tableTitle": "Pin Descriptions",
      "columns": [
        "PIN",
        "NAME",
        "DESCRIPTION"
      ],
      "rows": [
        {
          "PIN": "1",
          "NAME": "INTVcc",
          "DESCRIPTION": "Internal 3.6V regulator output. The internal power drivers and control circuits are powered from this voltage. Decouple this pin to power ground with a minimum of 4.7µF low ESR ceramic capacitor."
        },
        {
          "PIN": "2-12",
          "NAME": "SW",
          "DESCRIPTION": "Switch node connection of external inductor. Voltage swing of SW is from a diode voltage drop below ground to a diode voltage above PVIN."
        },
        {
          "PIN": "13",
          "NAME": "RUN",
          "DESCRIPTION": "Logic controlled RUN input. Do not leave this pin floating. Logic high activates the step-down regulator."
        },
        {
          "PIN": "14",
          "NAME": "AVPSEL",
          "DESCRIPTION": "Use this pin to select between three different load lines; tied to GND: 0.2%, float: 1%, INTVcc: 1.5%."
        },
        {
          "PIN": "15",
          "NAME": "PHSMD1/ ISEL",
          "DESCRIPTION": "Control inputs to the phase selector and ILIM option. A high or low state on this pin, in conjunction with the state of the PHSMD2/ILIM pin, determines the phase relationship between SYNC and the internal oscillator and between the internal oscillator and CLKOUT. When this pin is floated to mid rail (1/2 INTVcc), the PHSMD2/ILIM pin can be used to select between three lower ILIM settings."
        },
        {
          "PIN": "16",
          "NAME": "PHSMD2/ ILIM",
          "DESCRIPTION": "Control inputs to the phase selector and ILIM set. When PHSMD1/ISEL is high or low, this pin in conjunction with PHSMD1/ILIM determines the phasing between SYNC and the internal oscillator and between the internal oscillator and CLKOUT. When PHSMD1/ISEL is floated to mid rail (1/2 INTVcc), this pin can be used to select between three different lower ILIM settings."
        },
        {
          "PIN": "17",
          "NAME": "MODE",
          "DESCRIPTION": "Mode select pin. Tie MODE to GND for discontinuous mode of operation. Float or tie MODE to a voltage above 1V selects forced continuous mode."
        },
        {
          "PIN": "18",
          "NAME": "PGOOD",
          "DESCRIPTION": "Output power good with open-drain logic. PGOOD is pulled to ground when the voltage of the FB pin is not within ±6.5% of the internal 0.4V* reference.*0.4V: LT7153SPAV-0.4; 0.5V: LT7153SPAV"
        },
        {
          "PIN": "19-27",
          "NAME": "PVIN",
          "DESCRIPTION": "Power VIN. Input voltage to the on-chip power MOSFETs."
        },
        {
          "PIN": "28",
          "NAME": "SYNC/ SPREAD",
          "DESCRIPTION": "Spread spectrum select and oscillator synchronization pin. Tie SYNC/SPREAD to GND to disable spread spectrum operation; tie to INTVcc or float to start spread spectrum. Connect to an external clock to synchronize the system clock to the external clock and put the part in forced continuous mode."
        },
        {
          "PIN": "29",
          "NAME": "SVIN",
          "DESCRIPTION": "Signal VIN. Filtered input voltage to the on-chip 3.6V regulator. Bypass the signal into the SVIN pin through a 2.2Ω resistor in series with 10µF ceramic capacitor."
        },
        {
          "PIN": "30",
          "NAME": "CLKOUT",
          "DESCRIPTION": "Output clock signal for PolyPhase operation. The phase of CLKOUT with respect to SYNC is determined by the state of PHSMD1 and PHSMD2 pins. CLKOUT’s peak-to-peak amplitude is INTVcc to GND. Minimize the parasitic capacitance on this pin to reduce phase errors. When RUN is low, this pin defaults high."
        },
        {
          "PIN": "31",
          "NAME": "SGND",
          "DESCRIPTION": "Ground for signal ground."
        },
        {
          "PIN": "32",
          "NAME": "RT",
          "DESCRIPTION": "Switching frequency programming pin. Connect an external resistor from this pin to GND to program the frequency from 400kHz to 5MHz."
        },
        {
          "PIN": "33",
          "NAME": "ITH",
          "DESCRIPTION": "Error amplifier output and switching regulator compensation point. The current comparator’s trip threshold is linearly proportional to this voltage, whose normal range is from 0.3V to 1.3V."
        },
        {
          "PIN": "34",
          "NAME": "TRACK/SS",
          "DESCRIPTION": "Output tracking and soft-start pin. Allows to control the rise time of the output voltage. Connecting a voltage between 0V and 0.4V* on this pin relative to VOUT- bypasses the internal reference input to the error amplifier. Instead, it servos the FB pin relative to VOUT- to this voltage. There’s an internal 10µA pullup current from INTVcc to this pin; so putting a capacitor from this pin to VOUT- provides a soft-start function.*0.4V: LT7153SPAV-0.4; 0.5V: LT7153SPAV"
        },
        {
          "PIN": "35",
          "NAME": "FB",
          "DESCRIPTION": "Feedback input to the error amplifier of the step-down regulator. Connect the feedback resistor divider center tap to this pin. The output can be adjusted from 0.4V* to 4.5V.*0.4V: LT7153SPAV-0.4; 0.5V: LT7153SPAV"
        },
        {
          "PIN": "36",
          "NAME": "VOUT-",
          "DESCRIPTION": "Negative return of output rail. Connect this pin directly to the bottom terminal of the remote output capacitor near the load in order to minimize error incurred by voltage drops across the metal traces of the PCB."
        },
        {
          "PIN": "37",
          "NAME": "GND",
          "DESCRIPTION": "Exposed Pad."
        },
        {
          "PIN": "38-41",
          "NAME": "GND",
          "DESCRIPTION": "Corner Ground Pins."
        }
      ],
      "docOrder": 7
    },
    {
      "tableTitle": "Typical Performance Characteristics",
      "columns": [
        "Left Figure",
        "Left Figure Caption",
        "Right Figure",
        "Right Figure Caption"
      ],
      "rows": [
